<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-01-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-01-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="189" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d189">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                McCook</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 18.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                                </placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-01-05"><hi rend="italic">January</hi> 5, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have had the honor to receive from Mr.
                            Odell, the Hawaiian charge d’affaires to this country, a letter which
                            was addressed to me by Mr. de Varigny, minister for foreign affairs of
                            the Hawaiian kingdom, in which he expresses the appreciation by that
                            government of the courtesies shown by the government of the United
                            States to her Majesty the dowager Queen Emma, on her recent visit to
                            this country. The President authorizes me to assure the Hawaiian
                            government that he has read the communication referred to with much
                            satisfaction, and that it will be his constant desire to preserve the
                            most cordial and friendly relations with the government of Hawaii.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                        </closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Edward M. McCook,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>